{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-1281].
  {panel}

Currently the search results only cover the latest versions of pages and attachments. It might be a useful feature to be able to search ALL history.

Use case: I know there was a document containing "Apple" online at some stage, but right now I can't find it because someone has removed the word "Apple" from it in the latest version.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-1246].
  {panel}

I'm currently migrating lots of documentation into Confluence and it would be nice with a macro for automatic link creation (e.g. to external API documentation).

Basically I would like some way for me to decorate class names that would make them links to the MSDN-style documentation generated by NDoc (which uses a well defined naming convention for the html files, and is thus an ideal target for a macro of some sort).

It would also be nice if I could define link keywords, i.e. words that will always be converted to a link (with no additional formatting in the page source).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-1241].
  {panel}

JIRA has this already.

For software documenation purposes, it would be great to have a {bug} macro which would display a panel having a "bug" icon (preferably definable in space theme settings), a title and then a block of formattable content, eg:

{bug:title=Known Issues}
!someImage.gif!

Text _with_ formatting, etc.
{bug}

Likewise, it would be great to have a {tip} macro that would be almost identical only it would have a different icon (something like a lightbulb or whatever).

{tip:title=Qucker Editing}
!someImage.gif!

Text _with_ formatting, etc.
{tip}

There are probably several other little panels like this that would be really useful for standardising these things in software documentation such as {warning}, {howto}, etc.

{code}
AdlFormat2adeptSlideFormat["Online"].insert(0,"OR")
AdlFormat2adeptSlideFormat["Image"].insert(0,"OR")
{code}

becomes
{code}
AdlFormat2adeptSlideFormat[Brainstorm:"Online"].insert(0,"OR")
AdlFormat2adeptSlideFormat[Brainstorm:"Image"].insert(0,"OR")
{code}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-1193].
  {panel}

Confluence should warn if multiple people open a page for editing concurrently. JSPWiki has a nice implementation of this - when you open a page for edits you get a huge warning if someone opened the page during last half an hour and hasn't either cancelled or saved. The warning includes the name of the user who has opened the page. Saving (by anyone) removes the lock.

I assumed this was a standard feature and didn't even check if it's there or not but testing for it's existence revealed there's no warnings. :)
